{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Two primary generative paradigms have emerged in this context: diffusion models and autoregressive transformers.",
    "Diffusion Transformers Diffusion models synthesize data by learning to reverse a progressive noising process, typically through a sequence of denoising steps (Ho et al., 2020).",
    "In computer vision, Latent Diffusion Transformers (DiTs) have demonstrated strong performance by applying this principle in the latent space of a VAE (Peebles & Xie, 2022).",
    "More recently, diffusion-based techniques have been adapted to scientific modeling.",
    "For example, Kohl et al. (2024) proposed an autoregressive diffusion framework tailored for PDEs, particularly in turbulent settings where capturing stochasticity is essential."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
